36u32
37nvkm_pci_rd32(struct nvkm_pci *pci, u16 addr)
38{
39 return pci->func->rd32(pci, addr);
40}
41
42void
43nvkm_pci_wr08(struct nvkm_pci *pci, u16 addr, u8 data)
44{
45 pci->func->wr08(pci, addr, data);
46}
47
48void
49nvkm_pci_wr32(struct nvkm_pci *pci, u16 addr, u32 data)
50{
51 pci->func->wr32(pci, addr, data);
52}
53
54u32
55nvkm_pci_mask(struct nvkm_pci *pci, u16 addr, u32 mask, u32 value)
56{
57 u32 data = pci->func->rd32(pci, addr);
58 pci->func->wr32(pci, addr, (data & ~mask) | value);
59 return data;
60}
61
62void
63nvkm_pci_rom_shadow(struct nvkm_pci *pci, bool shadow)
64{
65 u32 data = nvkm_pci_rd32(pci, 0x0050);
66 if (shadow)
67 data |= 0x00000001;
68 else
69 data &= ~0x00000001;
70 nvkm_pci_wr32(pci, 0x0050, data);
71}
72
73static irqreturn_t
74nvkm_pci_intr(DRM_IRQ_ARGS)
75{
76 struct nvkm_pci *pci = arg;
77 struct nvkm_mc *mc = pci->subdev.device->mc;
78 bool handled = false;
79 if (likely(mc)) {
80 nvkm_mc_intr_unarm(mc);
81 if (pci->msi)
82 pci->func->msi_rearm(pci);
83 nvkm_mc_intr(mc, &handled);
84 nvkm_mc_intr_rearm(mc);
85 }
86 return handled ? IRQ_HANDLED : IRQ_NONE;
87}
88
89static int
90nvkm_pci_fini(struct nvkm_subdev *subdev, bool suspend)
91{
92 struct nvkm_pci *pci = nvkm_pci(subdev);
93
94#ifdef __NetBSD__
95 const struct pci_attach_args *pa = &pci->pdev->pd_pa;
96 if (pci->pci_intrcookie != NULL) {
97 pci_intr_disestablish(pa->pa_pc, pci->pci_intrcookie);
98 pci->pci_intrcookie = NULL;
99 }
100 if (pci->pci_ihp != NULL) {
101 pci_intr_release(pa->pa_pc, pci->pci_ihp, 1);
102 pci->pci_ihp = NULL;
103 }
104#else
105 if (pci->irq >= 0) {
106 free_irq(pci->irq, pci);
107 pci->irq = -1;
108 };
109#endif
110
111 if (pci->agp.bridge)
112 nvkm_agp_fini(pci);
113
114 return 0;
115}
116
117static int
118nvkm_pci_preinit(struct nvkm_subdev *subdev)
119{
120 struct nvkm_pci *pci = nvkm_pci(subdev);
121 if (pci->agp.bridge)
122 nvkm_agp_preinit(pci);
123 return 0;
124}
125
126static int
127nvkm_pci_init(struct nvkm_subdev *subdev)
128{
129 struct nvkm_pci *pci = nvkm_pci(subdev);
130 struct pci_dev *pdev = pci->pdev;
131 int ret;
132
133 if (pci->agp.bridge) {
134 ret = nvkm_agp_init(pci);
135 if (ret)
136 return ret;
137 }
138
139 if (pci->func->init)
140 pci->func->init(pci);
141
142#ifdef __NetBSD__
143 {
144 const struct pci_attach_args *pa = &pdev->pd_pa;
145 int counts[PCI_INTR_TYPE_SIZE] = {
146 [PCI_INTR_TYPE_INTX] = 1,
147 [PCI_INTR_TYPE_MSI] = 0,
148 [PCI_INTR_TYPE_MSIX] = 0,
149 };
150
151 /* XXX errno NetBSD->Linux */
152 ret = -pci_intr_alloc(pa, &pci->pci_ihp, counts, PCI_INTR_TYPE_INTX);
153 if (ret)
154 return ret;
155 pci->pci_intrcookie = pci_intr_establish_xname(pa->pa_pc,
156 pci->pci_ihp[0], IPL_DRM, nvkm_pci_intr, pci,
157 device_xname(pci_dev_dev(pdev)));
158 if (pci->pci_intrcookie == NULL)
159 return -EIO; /* XXX er? */
160 }
161#else
162 ret = request_irq(pdev->irq, nvkm_pci_intr, IRQF_SHARED, "nvkm", pci);
163 if (ret)
164 return ret;
165
166 pci->irq = pdev->irq;
167#endif
168
169 /* Ensure MSI interrupts are armed, for the case where there are
170 * already interrupts pending (for whatever reason) at load time.
171 */
172 if (pci->msi)
173 pci->func->msi_rearm(pci);
174
175 return ret;
176}
177
178static void *
179nvkm_pci_dtor(struct nvkm_subdev *subdev)
180{
181 struct nvkm_pci *pci = nvkm_pci(subdev);
182 nvkm_agp_dtor(pci);
183 if (pci->msi)
184 pci_disable_msi(pci->pdev);
185 return nvkm_pci(subdev);
186}
187
188static const struct nvkm_subdev_func
189nvkm_pci_func = {
190 .dtor = nvkm_pci_dtor,
191 .preinit = nvkm_pci_preinit,
192 .init = nvkm_pci_init,
193 .fini = nvkm_pci_fini,
194};
195
196int
197nvkm_pci_new_(const struct nvkm_pci_func *func, struct nvkm_device *device,
198 int index, struct nvkm_pci **ppci)
199{
200 struct nvkm_pci *pci;
201
202 if (!(pci = *ppci = kzalloc(sizeof(**ppci), GFP_KERNEL)))
203 return -ENOMEM;
204 nvkm_subdev_ctor(&nvkm_pci_func, device, index, 0, &pci->subdev);
205 pci->func = func;
206 pci->pdev = device->func->pci(device)->pdev;
207#ifndef __NetBSD__
208 pci->irq = -1;
209#endif
210
211 if (device->type == NVKM_DEVICE_AGP)
212 nvkm_agp_ctor(pci);
213
214 switch (pci->pdev->device & 0x0ff0) {
215 case 0x00f0:
216 case 0x02e0:
217 /* BR02? NFI how these would be handled yet exactly */
218 break;
219 default:
220 switch (device->chipset) {
221 case 0xaa:
222 /* reported broken, nv also disable it */
223 break;
224 default:
225 pci->msi = true;
226 break;
227 }
228 }
229
230#ifdef __BIG_ENDIAN
231 pci->msi = false;
232#endif
233
234 pci->msi = nvkm_boolopt(device->cfgopt, "NvMSI", pci->msi);
235 if (pci->msi && func->msi_rearm) {
236 pci->msi = pci_enable_msi(pci->pdev) == 0;
237 if (pci->msi)
238 nvkm_debug(&pci->subdev, "MSI enabled\n");
239 } else {
240 pci->msi = false;
241 }
242
243 return 0;
244}
